{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Predictions, produced by expectations encoded within the generative model, underpin perception and action.",
    "If predictions fail to match the incoming sensory data, 'prediction errors' are generated that propagate upward through the hierarchy of the generative model, driving action and revised prediction.",
    "Not all predictions are of equal importance or reliability; a mechanism known as 'precision weighting' modulates the impact within the overall system that sets of errors have: high weighting drives learning and further engagement, while low weighting renders error units relatively impotent (Clark, 2013b (Clark,, 2016)).",
    "Precision also applies to action, representing the degree of confidence that the system has in an action to reduce uncertainty, central for adaptation.",
    "Prediction errors can be minimised in two ways."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Not all predictions are of equal importance or reliability; a mechanism known as 'precision weighting' modulates the impact within the overall system that sets of errors have: high weighting drives learning and further engagement, while low weighting renders error units relatively impotent (Clark, 2013b (Clark,, 2016))."
